        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 6:38PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 637 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Good Hope, or near Macomb, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could cause minor tree limb damage and blow
around unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Good Hope around 645 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
